    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "There are three pkg-config files in the repo:\r\n- libtoxcore.pc.in\r\n- libtoxav.pc.in\r\n- other/pkgconfig/toxcore.pc.in\r\n\r\nCMake is building and installing toxcore.pc, which doesn't look right.\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "@ehmry yes this is correct.\r\nthe autotools and cmake build produce different results.\r\nautotools makes 3 libs, cmake puts everything into 1 lib.\r\n\r\nautotools:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlibtoxav.a\r\nlibtoxav.la\r\nlibtoxcore.a\r\nlibtoxcore.la\r\nlibtoxencryptsave.a\r\nlibtoxencryptsave.la\r\npkgconfig/libtoxav.pc\r\npkgconfig/libtoxcore.pc\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\ncmake:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlibtoxcore.a\r\nlibtoxcore.so\r\nlibtoxcore.so.2\r\nlibtoxcore.so.2.18.0\r\npkgconfig/toxcore.pc\r\n\r\ncat pkgconfig/toxcore.pc\r\nprefix=/usr/local\r\nlibdir=${prefix}/lib\r\nincludedir=${prefix}/include\r\n\r\nName: toxcore\r\nDescription: Tox protocol library\r\nRequires.private: libsodium opus vpx\r\nVersion: 0.2.18\r\nLibs: -L${libdir} -ltoxcore\r\nLibs.private: -lpthread -lnsl -lrt\r\nCflags: -I${includedir}\r\n\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2022-11-03T19:17:08Z",
